The paper focuses on personalized recommendation and the exploitation of rich structured information provided by knowledge graphs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), and Databases (cs.DB). Among these, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely categories as the paper proposes a reinforcement learning approach for recommendation and interpretability.
